From 5d31896fe02927ded5be2bf9e22d81e8895ee4ee Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 11:46:09 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): plan/quota gate at Supervisor entry
 (flag-gated, fail-open)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Audit issue #1: plan/quota was enforced only on the web path; Telegram,
Slack, and Ignition surfaces had none. Adds ONE enforcement point at
Supervisor.process() so every adapter inherits it.

- mira-bots/shared/quota.py: async check_quota(tenant_id) -> (allowed,
  reason). Reimplements the mira-core check_tier_limit tier query
  (tenants.tier -> tier_limits.daily_requests -> today's
  knowledge_entries count) using this package's own NeonDB pattern
  (NEON_DATABASE_URL, lazy sqlalchemy, run_in_executor + timeout —
  same precedent as decision_trace.py). No cross-module import.
- Gated behind ENFORCE_PLAN_QUOTA (default OFF: no DB call, no
  behavior change — safe to merge). Fail-OPEN on missing tenant_id,
  unset DB URL, unknown tenant, DB error, or timeout.
- Wired at the top of Supervisor.process() BEFORE inference; blocked
  tenants get a short technician-friendly upgrade message through the
  normal str return type. UNS gate / greeting / safety paths untouched.
- tests/test_quota_gate.py: 8 offline tests (mock DB) — flag off/unset
  -> no DB call; over-quota -> block; DB error / missing tenant /
  missing URL -> allow; Supervisor wiring (block short-circuits
  process_full; allowed turn proceeds).
